## Description {#details}

A helper data structure to hold the operands of a vector of instructions.

This supports a fixed vector length for all operand vectors.

Definition at line 1988 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/vectorize/slpvectorizer-cpp">SLPVectorizer.cpp</a>.

## Enumerations

### enum class  {#a75123632e7d04bee5f5ae50f9c208bca}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum class llvm::slpvectorizer::BoUpSLP::VLOperands::ReorderingMode "
 labels = {["strong"]}>
During operand reordering, we are trying to select the operand at lane that matches best with the operand at the neighboring lane.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="a75123632e7d04bee5f5ae50f9c208bcaaf19dbf2edb3a0bd74b0524d960ff21eb" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Load">
Matching loads to consecutive memory addresses
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a75123632e7d04bee5f5ae50f9c208bcaa5782f6bdd633ac305e1e625779f96a77" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Opcode">
Matching instructions based on opcode (same or alternate)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a75123632e7d04bee5f5ae50f9c208bcaacb17869fe51048b5a5c4c6106551a255" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Constant">
Matching constants
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a75123632e7d04bee5f5ae50f9c208bcaa5b9bf50c6579a978e5c1104bf8787651" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Splat">
Matching the same instruction multiple times (broadcast)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a75123632e7d04bee5f5ae50f9c208bcaad7c8c85bf79bbe1b7188497c32c3b0ca" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Failed">
We failed to create a vectorizable group
</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

Our selection is based on the type of value we are looking for. For example, if the neighboring lane has a load, we need to look for a load that is accessing a consecutive address. These strategies are summarized in the &#39;ReorderingMode&#39; enumerator.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/vectorize/slpvectorizer-cpp/#l02036">2036</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/vectorize/slpvectorizer-cpp">SLPVectorizer.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
